[size=4][b]What[/b][/size]

[size=3]A buildable trunk Gerry empties at midnight — any items you drop in get sold at a share of their vendor value, no travel required. Gerry takes a cut, which shrinks as your character progresses, so it's a convenience tax rather than a replacement for selling directly.[/size]

[size=3][b]How to unlock and upgrade[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Stage 1 — Woodworking tech[/b]: initial unlock. Ten slots, max 50 of each item. Gerry takes his biggest cut.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Stage 2 — Engineer tech[/b]: twenty slots, max 50 of each item. Build from the same construction menu to upgrade.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Stage 3 — Jeweler tech[/b]: twenty slots, max 100 of each item. Gerry takes a smaller cut.[/size]
[*][size=3]Only one trunk can exist at a time. Destroy and rebuild if you want to relocate.[/size]
[/list]

[size=3][b]Selling behaviour[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Drop in, don't take out[/b] — once an item is in the trunk it belongs to Gerry. No take-back. This is a one-way stockpile by design, not a regular chest.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Gerry visits at midnight[/b] — when the game clock flips to 00:00, Gerry walks over, empties the trunk, and leaves you a cash pile at dawn.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Item price tooltips[/b] — optional. When on, each item in the trunk shows what Gerry will pay you for it. Off if you prefer the element of surprise.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Sold-item messages[/b] — optional floating text above the keeper showing what just got sold and for how much.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Cinematic framing[/b] — on by default, the camera focuses on Gerry's visit and gameplay pauses. Turn off if you'd rather keep playing while Gerry works in the background.[/size]
[/list]

[size=3][b]Other[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Intro message[/b] — on first install, a short in-game dialog explains what to expect. Dismiss once and it stays dismissed.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Main menu update notice[/b] — flags when a newer version of this mod (or other mods in my collection) is on Nexus. Click an entry to open its Nexus page. Opt-out via "Check for Updates".[/size]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Other mods of mine you might like[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/62]Where's Ma' Storage[/url] — pools every container's contents into one shared inventory. Pair with Gerry's Junk Trunk to offload the junk you don't want clogging the pool.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/51]Auto-Loot Heavies[/url] — teleports timber, stone, marble, and ore to the nearest stockpile. Combine to keep storage tidy: loot auto-routes to stockpiles, overflow goes in the trunk.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/61]Beam Me Up Gerry[/url] — teleport between the zones you've visited. Faster runs to the trunk between farming sessions.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/67]Economy Reloaded[/url] — removes vendor inflation/deflation. Stabilises what the trunk pays out over time.[/size]
[/list]

